In this article, President Donald J. Trump issues a proclamation declaring September 15 through October 15 as National Hispanic Heritage Month. The proclamation highlights the contributions of Hispanic Americans to American culture and society, emphasizing their commitment to faith, family, and country. The president also discusses the importance of educational opportunity for Hispanic Americans, mentioning school choice programs and the White House Hispanic Prosperity Initiative. He notes the administration's efforts to increase economic opportunities for Hispanic Americans through job creation and investment in Hispanic-American communities. The article highlights positive outcomes of these policies, such as increased graduation rates and income levels for Hispanic Americans. The president concludes by expressing his commitment to rebuilding the economy and ensuring opportunity for all Americans.